def: To take (any one) by force or fear, and against one's will,with intent to carry to another place. Abbott.You may reason or expostulate with the parents, but never attempt tokidnap their children, and to make proselytes of them. Whately.
To impart metallic properties to; to impregnate with a metal.[R.]
Not reasonable; irrational; immoderate; exorbitant.-- Un*rea"son*a*ble*ness, n.-- Un*rea"son*a*bly, adv.
Resembling a fox in his characteristic qualities; cunning;artful; foxy.
A sea open to all nations. See Mare clausum.
Among Mohammedans, a warrior champion or veteran, esp. in thedestruction of infidels.
